\details{
\subsection{Workflow}{

A complete \code{htaBIM} analysis follows five steps:
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Population} -- estimate the annual eligible patient population using
\code{\link[=bim_population]{bim_population()}}
\item \strong{Market share} -- specify treatment shares with and without the new
drug using \code{\link[=bim_market_share]{bim_market_share()}}
\item \strong{Costs} -- build per-patient annual costs by treatment and category
using \code{\link[=bim_costs]{bim_costs()}}
\item \strong{Model} -- assemble and run the BIM using \code{\link[=bim_model]{bim_model()}}
\item \strong{Outputs} -- extract tables, plots, and reports using \code{\link[=bim_table]{bim_table()}},
\code{\link[=plot.bim_model]{plot.bim_model()}}, and \code{\link[=bim_report]{bim_report()}}
}
}

